<TITLE> Few more cold days forecast </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 3 (bdnews24.com) With the temperatures falling in northern Bangladesh, mild cold wave in different parts of the country may continue for few more days, the Met Office said on Saturday. "Mild cold wave might continue in different areas including the Rajshahi division," weather official Bazlur Rashid said. "If the high continental weather pressure, prevailing now in West Bengal, moves further eastward, temperatures will go further down," he said. "The eastern zone feels cold because of the chill carried by the eastward cold wave," he said. A Met bulletin said: "Cold wave was also felt in Rangamati, Comilla, Srimangal, Jessore, Chuadanga and Barisal since Friday and temperatures fell further on Saturday." On Saturday, the lowest temperature in the country was recorded at 8 degrees Celsius in Rajshahi and Srimangal. The day's low in the capital was 12.8 degrees Celsius. The forecast till 6 pm Sunday said weather all over the country would mainly remain dry with the sky remaining partially cloudy. But from midnight, moderate to heavy fog may envelope the northern part and the river basin. At other places fog at light to moderate scale may continue. Cold wave may continue in Rahshai division, Rangamati, Comilla, Srimangal, Jessore, Chuadanga and Barisal. Weather at night may almost remain unchanged. bdn
